<br>
It's not intended to be an effort at starting any particular project, but the eventual goal, should enough interest be generated, would be to come up with a semi-workable strategy for approaching one.<br>
<br>
If this sounds at all interesting to you, please read the post in the &quot;Manifesto&quot; section at:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/bfocusmmog">pub41.ezboard.com/bfocusmmog</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Thank you<br>
-Emcius <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucloudien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cloudien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/9/01 9:17:29 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To anyone interested in open-source and MMOG development</span><hr size=1> It's an awesome idea.  There is already a project like this though:<br>
<br>
http://www.worldforge.org<br>
<br>
My suggestion would be to offer them a helping hand rather than starting your own separate project, unless you have a good reason to.<br>
<br>
I'm one of those who's always saying that if KDE and GNOME stopped fighting and worked together we'd have an awesome Linux desktop by now, rather than two "usable" ones :)  I'd say the same would go for an MMOG. <p>-- <BR>
